Le Cinema Club
Now showing... Here's a list of films that I watched for the first time on this site and admired. I remembered to save the descriptions of some of these for reference.

MOUNE Ô by MAXIME JEAN-BAPTISTE
Moune Ô was made using footage from a television report on the premiere of Alain Maline’s Jean Galmot Aventurier (1990), a biopic about the eponymous French gold prospector and subject of critique in Jean-Baptiste’s previous short Nou Voix (2018). Pausing, rewinding, and commenting on the footage from the report, Jean-Baptiste emphasizes how the pageantry on view did not correspond with the lived-experience of Guianese immigrants in Paris.
